.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH mpa 1  "mpa 0.8.6" 
.SH NAME
mpa \- Moshpit agent — holds identity keys in memory and serves them over a Unix socket
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmpa\fR [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR]... [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR]... [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Moshpit agent — holds identity keys in memory and serves them over a Unix socket
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Turn up logging verbosity (multiple will turn it up more)
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Turn down logging verbosity (multiple will turn it down more)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
mpa\-start(1)
Start the agent daemon
.TP
mpa\-add\-key(1)
Add an identity key to the agent
.TP
mpa\-list(1)
List identities held by the agent
.TP
mpa\-remove\-key(1)
Remove an identity from the agent
.TP
mpa\-lock(1)
Lock the agent (clear keys from memory)
.TP
mpa\-unlock(1)
Unlock the agent (reload keys from vault)
.TP
mpa\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH VERSION
v0.8.6
